Many if not almost all static resources (images, stylesheets and javascripts) are being pulled via the resource manager which generates urls with {{/s/}} prefix. This prefix is also included in the mappings for the {{sessioninview}} filter in {{web.xml}}.

{code:xml}
    <filter-mapping>
        <filter-name>sessioninview</filter-name>
        <url-pattern>/s/*</url-pattern>
    </filter-mapping>
{code}

This causes connections to be leased from the connection pool unnecessarily and in case that there are misbehaving clients that block on reading the response (we see those quite often), this could lead to an unnecessary DoS situation because of lack of db connections to serve legitimate requests.

Most of the asset files that Confluence uses are static and don't require db connection, there is only a handful of those that do (certain stylesheets?). It would be good to separate these two and map the {{sessioninview}} filter only to the second group.

