When creating a qwiki page that discusses C++ classes it creates a lot of false links.  This is because the camelback linking is turned on.  So anything that LooksLikeThis automatically has a link created for it.  It can be worked around by putting {nolink:LooksLikeThis} or {nl:LooksLikeThis}, but it can be a pain to do when there are lots of names like that.  What often happens is that people don't bother, which creates a lot of red links to nowhere.

It may not be feasible to disable camelback linking everywhere, but it would be nice to be able to disable it on a per page basis.

